You can also use undocumented T-SQL, see here &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.lessthandot.com/index.php/Read_the_error_log_with_T-SQL&quot;&gt; Read the error log with T-SQL&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
here are some commands&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
--Read current error log&lt;br /&gt;
EXEC xp_readerrorlog 0&lt;br /&gt;
GO&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
--Search for backup database messages&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
EXEC sp_readerrorlog 0, 1, &#039;Database backed up&#039;&lt;br /&gt;
GO
